<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="30">
The historical delimitation of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1830" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been shown to be highly polyphyletic, and large-scale taxonomic realignment and recognition of new genera has been undertaken to ensure strict monophyly of genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Mols, JB" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" pagination="490 - 494" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364408785679752" refId="B11" refString="Mols, JB, Kessler, PJA, Rogstad, SH, Saunders, RMK, 2008. Reassignment of six Polyalthia species to the new genus Maasia (Annonaceae): molecular and morphological congruence. Systematic Botany 33: 490 - 494, 10.1600/036364408785679752" title="Reassignment of six Polyalthia species to the new genus Maasia (Annonaceae): molecular and morphological congruence." url="10.1600/036364408785679752" volume="33" year="2008">Mols et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Saunders, RMK" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" pagination="1407 - 1416" refId="B18" refString="Saunders, RMK, Su, YCF, Xue, B, 2011. Phylogenetic affinities of Polyalthia species (Annonaceae) with columellar-sulcate pollen: enlarging the Madagascan endemic genus Fenerivia. Taxon 60: 1407 - 1416" title="Phylogenetic affinities of Polyalthia species (Annonaceae) with columellar-sulcate pollen: enlarging the Madagascan endemic genus Fenerivia." volume="60" year="2011">Saunders et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" pagination="17 - 26" publicationUrl="10.1080/14772000.2010.542497" refId="B24" refString="Xue, B, Su, YCF, Mols, JB, Kessler, PJA, Saunders, RMK, 2011. Further fragmentation of the polyphyletic genus Polyalthia (Annonaceae): molecular phylogenetic support for a broader delimitation of Marsypopetalum. Systematics and Biodiversity 9: 17 - 26, 10.1080/14772000.2010.542497" title="Further fragmentation of the polyphyletic genus Polyalthia (Annonaceae): molecular phylogenetic support for a broader delimitation of Marsypopetalum." url="10.1080/14772000.2010.542497" volume="9" year="2011">Xue et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" pagination="1021 - 1039" refId="B25" refString="Xue, B, Su, YCF, Thomas,, DC, Saunders, RMK, 2012. Pruning the polyphyletic genus Polyalthia (Annonaceae) and resurrecting the genus Monoon. Taxon 61: 1021 - 1039" title="Pruning the polyphyletic genus Polyalthia (Annonaceae) and resurrecting the genus Monoon." volume="61" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" refId="B26" refString="Xue, B, Thomas, DC, Chaowasku, T, Johnson, DM, Saunders, RMK, in press. Molecular phylogenetic support for the taxonomic merger of Fitzalania and Meiogyne (Annonaceae): new nomenclatural combinations under the conserved name Meiogyne. Systematic Botany." title="Molecular phylogenetic support for the taxonomic merger of Fitzalania and Meiogyne (Annonaceae): new nomenclatural combinations under the conserved name Meiogyne. Systematic Botany." year="in press">in press</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chaowasku, T" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" pagination="33 - 56" refId="B1" refString="Chaowasku, T, Johnson, DM, Van der, Ham RWJM, Chatrou, LW, 2012. Characterization of Hubera (Annonaceae), a new genus segregated from Polyalthia and allied to Miliusa. Phytotaxa 69: 33 - 56" title="Characterization of Hubera (Annonaceae), a new genus segregated from Polyalthia and allied to Miliusa." volume="69" year="2012">Chaowasku et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). As part of this series of taxonomic revisions, chloroplast DNA regions were sequenced from eight species from the Melanesian island of Fiji (Xue, 2013) that had previously been assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1830" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Phylogenetic analysis of this data revealed that most of these species align with either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T.Chaowasku" authorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Hubera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Hubera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chaowasku, T" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" pagination="33 - 56" refId="B1" refString="Chaowasku, T, Johnson, DM, Van der, Ham RWJM, Chatrou, LW, 2012. Characterization of Hubera (Annonaceae), a new genus segregated from Polyalthia and allied to Miliusa. Phytotaxa 69: 33 - 56" title="Characterization of Hubera (Annonaceae), a new genus segregated from Polyalthia and allied to Miliusa." volume="69" year="2012">Chaowasku et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" refId="B23" refString="Xue, B, 2013. Molecular phylogenetics of Polyalthia (Annonaceae): identifying clades and morphological synapomorphies in a large polyphyletic genus. Unpublished PhD thesis, The University of Hong Kong." title="Molecular phylogenetics of Polyalthia (Annonaceae): identifying clades and morphological synapomorphies in a large polyphyletic genus. Unpublished PhD thesis, The University of Hong Kong." year="2013">Xue 2013</bibRefCitation>
) or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miquel" authorityYear="1865" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Meiogyne" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Meiogyne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" refId="B23" refString="Xue, B, 2013. Molecular phylogenetics of Polyalthia (Annonaceae): identifying clades and morphological synapomorphies in a large polyphyletic genus. Unpublished PhD thesis, The University of Hong Kong." title="Molecular phylogenetics of Polyalthia (Annonaceae): identifying clades and morphological synapomorphies in a large polyphyletic genus. Unpublished PhD thesis, The University of Hong Kong." year="2013">Xue 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" refId="B26" refString="Xue, B, Thomas, DC, Chaowasku, T, Johnson, DM, Saunders, RMK, in press. Molecular phylogenetic support for the taxonomic merger of Fitzalania and Meiogyne (Annonaceae): new nomenclatural combinations under the conserved name Meiogyne. Systematic Botany." title="Molecular phylogenetic support for the taxonomic merger of Fitzalania and Meiogyne (Annonaceae): new nomenclatural combinations under the conserved name Meiogyne. Systematic Botany." year="in press">Xue et al. in press</bibRefCitation>
), although one species, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A.C.Sm., which was sequenced from the type material, is nested within the 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Goniothalamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, B" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" refId="B23" refString="Xue, B, 2013. Molecular phylogenetics of Polyalthia (Annonaceae): identifying clades and morphological synapomorphies in a large polyphyletic genus. Unpublished PhD thesis, The University of Hong Kong." title="Molecular phylogenetics of Polyalthia (Annonaceae): identifying clades and morphological synapomorphies in a large polyphyletic genus. Unpublished PhD thesis, The University of Hong Kong." year="2013">Xue 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from fruiting material (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, AC" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" pagination="533 - 549" publicationUrl="10.2307/2481400" refId="B19" refString="Smith, AC, 1943. Studies on Pacific island plants-III. New and noteworthy flowering plants from Fiji. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 70: 533 - 549, 10.2307/2481400" title="Studies on Pacific island plants-III. New and noteworthy flowering plants from Fiji." url="10.2307/2481400" volume="70" year="1943">Smith 1943</bibRefCitation>
), and it is likely that its incorrect generic affiliation was due to the absence of flowers, which are very different in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1830" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Goniothalamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequent phylogenetic analyses with a larger taxon sampling (C.C. Tang et al., unpubl.) have revealed 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister to the Fijian species 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="monospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Goniothalamus monospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Baill.) R.M.K.Saunders with strong support (posterior clade probability = 1; bootstrap support = 96%); these two species are morphologically distinct, as 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seeds lack the broad lateral testa wings that are diagnostic of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="monospermus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Goniothalamus monospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Van Setten, AK" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" refId="B21" refString="Van Setten, AK, Koek-Noorman, J, 1992. Fruits and seeds of Annonaceae: morphology and its significance for classification and identification. Bibliotheca Botanica 142: 1-101, pl. 1-50." title="Fruits and seeds of Annonaceae: morphology and its significance for classification and identification. Bibliotheca Botanica 142: 1 - 101, pl. 1 - 50." year="1992">Van Setten and Koek-Noorman 1992</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 39i). The transfer of the name 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Polyalthia angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Annonaceae" genus="Goniothalamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Goniothalamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is accordingly validated here.
</paragraph>
